Better World Drops Most Since October 2008 in Thailand After Share Offer

-- B y   T o n y   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-04-26T04:51:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/better-world-drops-most-since-october-2008-in-thailand-after-share-offer.html
Better World Green Pcl (BWG) , a Thai
provider of waste-management services, fell the most in more
than two years in Bangkok trading after saying it may issue new
shares to existing investors.  The stock dropped 14 percent to 1.83 baht as of 11:45 a.m.
local time, the biggest decline since October 2008.  The company may issue 320 million new shares and offer
investors one new share for each one held, it said today in a
regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Jordan in Bangkok at 
